Cisco-IOS-XR-ethernet-cfm-oper API API Reference

API generated from Cisco-IOS-XR-ethernet-cfm-oper@2017-10-06.yang

API Endpoint
http://{Controller-IP}:{Controller-Port}/restconf/operational/network-topology:network-topology/topology/topology-netconf/node/{{router}}/yang-ext:mount/
URL '/' code: %2F
Schemes: http
Version: 1.0.0

Paths

CFM - Retrieve

GET Cisco-IOS-XR-ethernet-cfm-oper:cfm/

Retrieve operation of resource: cfm

200 OK
cfm_schema

Successful operation

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

"sla-synthetic-loss-operations-disabled": "boolean", In-progress Ethernet SLA synthetic loss\nmeasurement operations are disabled due to\nsatellite having synthetic loss measurement\nresponder-only capabilities.

        
"service-bridge-domain": { BD/XC ID for the MEP's Service, or Service name\nif the Service is 'down-only'

          
"evi": "integer", EVPN ID for VLAN-aware flexible cross-connects

          
"group": "string", Name of the Bridge/XConnect Group

          
"name": "string", Name of the Bridge Domain/XConnect

          
"remote-ce-id": "integer", Remote Customer Edge Identifier (CE-ID)

          
"ce-id": "integer", Local Customer Edge Identifier (CE-ID)

          
"bridge-domain-id-format": "string" Bridge domain identifier format

        },
        
"ccm-interval-not-supported": "boolean", CCM Interval is less than minimum interval\nsupported by hardware

        
"offload-no-cross-check": "boolean", The MEP should be offloaded but crosscheck has\nnot been configured.

        
"no-service": "boolean", The MEP's Service is not configured

        
"offload-multiple-local-mep": "boolean", Multiple offloaded MEPs on the same interface\nare not supported.

        
"no-mlacp": "boolean", The EFP is a bundle and the mLACP mode is not\nyet known.

        
"satellite-id": "integer", ID of the satellite

        
"fatal-offload-error": "boolean", The platform returned a fatal error when passed\nthe offload session.

        
"bridge-domain-not-in-bd-infra": "boolean", A BD/XC specified in the MEG config, but it does\nnot exist globally.

        
"sla-loopback-operations-disabled": "boolean", In-progress Ethernet SLA loopback operations are\ndisabled due to satellite having loopback\nresponder-only capabilities.

        
"mep": { The MEP that has errors

          
"level": "string", Domain level

          
"mep-id": "integer", MEP ID

          
"domain-name": "string", Domain name

          
"maintenance-point-type": "string", Type of Maintenance Point

          
"service-name": "string", Service name

          
"interface": "string" Interface

        },
        
"satellite-error-string": "string", Error string returned from satellite

        
"no-interface-type": "boolean", We haven't yet been able to look up the\ninterface type to find whether the interface is\na bundle.

        
"satellite-capabilities": { Satellite Capabilities

          
"delay-measurement": { Delay Measurement

            
"controller": "boolean", Controller

            
"responder": "boolean" Responder

          },
          
"synthetic-loss-measurement": { Synthetic Loss Measurement

          },

        },

"evi": "integer", EVPN ID for VLAN-aware flexible cross-connects

PROTOCOLS - Retrieve

GET Cisco-IOS-XR-infra-sla-oper:sla/protocols/

200 OK
a1_protocols_schema

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

STATISTICS-ON-DEMAND-CURRENTS - Retrieve

GET Cisco-IOS-XR-infra-sla-oper:sla/protocols/ethernet/statistics-on-demand-currents/

Retrieve operation of resource: statistics-on-demand-currents

200 OK
a1_statistics-on-demand-currents_schema

Successful operation

400 Bad Request

Internal Error

"suspect-probe-restarted": "boolean", Results suspect as probe restarted mid-way\nthrough the bucket

        
"average": "string", Mean of the results in the probe, in\nmicroseconds or millionths of a percent

        
"suspect-multiple-buckets": "boolean" Buckets stored for the metric

      }
    ],
    
"config": { Configuration of the metric

      
"metric-type": "string", Type of metric to which this configuration\napplies

      
"bins-width": "integer", Width of each bin into which to aggregate. 0 if\nno aggregation. For SLM, the units of this value\nare in single units of percent; for LMM they are\nin tenths of percent; for other measurements\nthey are in milliseconds.

      
"bucket-size": "integer", Size of buckets into which measurements are\ncollected

      
"buckets-archive": "integer", Maximum number of buckets to store in memory

      
"bins-count": "integer", Total number of bins into which to aggregate. 0\nif no aggregation.

      
"bucket-size-unit": "string" Whether bucket size is 'per-probe' or 'probes'

    }
  }
}
